---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Contact & corrections — Biochemistry-pedia" description="Found an error or a slop artifact? Tell us and we'll fix it.">
  <article class="wrap prose-col" style="padding-top: var(--ddp-space-12)">
    <p class="eyebrow">Contact &amp; corrections</p>
    <h1>See something wrong? Tell us.</h1>

    <p>
      This is an evolving project. Many of the lecture slides use AI-assisted
      imagery, which means a chemical structure is occasionally drawn wrong or
      oriented oddly — &ldquo;slop&rdquo; artifacts that slip past us. The live 3D
      molecules in each lesson&rsquo;s sidebar are the accurate reference; the slides
      are a conceptual framework. We flag known issues right on the affected slides
      and fix them as we catch them.
    </p>

    <h2>Spotted a correction?</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href="mailto:deppmann@gmail.com?subject=Biochemistry-pedia%20correction">deppmann@gmail.com</a>
      with the lesson, the slide or section, and what looks off. A screenshot helps.
      We read every one and we&rsquo;ll get it fixed.
    </p>

    <p class="src-meta">
      A &ldquo;slop bounty&rdquo; for the sharpest-eyed corrections is something we
      may add down the road. For now, thank you for helping make this better.
    </p>

    <p><a href="/">← Back to lessons</a></p>
  </article>

  <style>
    .eyebrow {
      font-family: var(--ddp-font-mono);
      font-size: var(--ddp-text-xs);
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ddp-color-accent);
    }
    .src-meta {
      color: var(--ddp-color-muted);
      font-size: var(--ddp-text-sm);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
